    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1951-11-24T07:30:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1951-11-24T07:30:00-05:00" n="368"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d368">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">689.90D/11–2451: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Afghanistan</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Merrell</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Kabul</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1951-11-24T17:00:00+04:30"
                            >November 24, 1951—5 p. m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>250. While I fully agree we shld continue to urge <gloss target="#t_GOA1"
                        >GOA</gloss> to talk directly with <gloss target="#t_GOP1">GOP</gloss> re
                    their common problems (<gloss target="#t_Deptel1">Deptel</gloss> 165, November
                    15), I am not so sure we shld not give further consideration <gloss
                        target="#t_PriMin1">PriMin</gloss>’s offer (<gloss target="#t_Embtel1"
                        >Embtel</gloss> 231, Nov 8). It occurs to me that <gloss target="#t_GOP1"
                        >GOP</gloss> itself <pb facs="0537" n="2001" xml:id="pg_2001"/> might be
                    prepared to envisage a US undertaking (in which it was made clear that support
                    of Afghan cause not included) that Afghan–Pashtun case be given a hearing a few
                    years from now, since by so doing <gloss target="#t_GOP1">GOP</gloss> would
                    remove immediate annoyance which no doubt has bearing on its dispute over
                    Kashmir. In any case, I believe it wld strengthen <gloss target="#t_PriMin1"
                        >PriMin</gloss>’s hand in his evident attempts to chart a more moderate
                    course if we cld give him some encouragement and at the same time bolster our
                    primary thesis that, whatever may be the merits of Afghan–Pashtun case, at the
                    present time we shld all present a united front against Commie aggression.</p>
                <p>Dept pass Karachi. Sent Dept 250; rptd info Karachi 41, London unn.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Merrell</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
